    "body": "@dapplion yeah from the 1st look it seems like it uses its own score params\r\n```ts\r\n      ...options,\r\n      scoreParams: createPeerScoreParams(options.scoreParams),\r\n```\r\n\r\nhowever `options` is from lodestar GossipSub so `createPeerScoreParams(options.scoreParams)` really get data from lodestar GossipSub\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nexport function createPeerScoreParams (p: Partial<PeerScoreParams> = {}): PeerScoreParams {\r\n  return {\r\n    ...defaultPeerScoreParams,\r\n    ...p,\r\n    topics: p.topics\r\n      ? Object.entries(p.topics)\r\n        .reduce((topics, [topic, topicScoreParams]) => {\r\n          topics[topic] = createTopicScoreParams(topicScoreParams)\r\n          return topics\r\n        }, {} as Record<string, TopicScoreParams>)\r\n      : {}\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```",
